T (kicking an apostrophe is like kicking a kitten!); or the new girls (especially the recurrent young beauty consisting of horizontal shadings); or the frame house made so mysteriously opaque by the occlusion of N,O,P and Q; or the labyrinthiform person peering at the portrait of a fellow labyrinthian.

Your visit to Montreux was a long time ago, and we do hope that you will come again soon!

Best greetings from both of us.





Vladimir Nabokov





TO: SAMUEL ROSOFF

ALS (XEROX), 1 p.





